1
00:00:56,173 --> 00:00:59,009
FILING FOR LOVE

2
00:01:02,054 --> 00:01:03,055
REPORTING MS. JOO IN-A

3
00:01:03,138 --> 00:01:04,265
<i>Joo In-a's</i>

4
00:01:05,182 --> 00:01:06,225
<i>having an affair?</i>

5
00:01:09,853 --> 00:01:11,939
HEAD OF AUDIT JOO IN-A

6
00:01:12,815 --> 00:01:14,233
Will you hear me out?

7
00:01:14,316 --> 00:01:16,652
It's really a misunderstanding,
Ms. Joo.

8
00:01:16,735 --> 00:01:18,862
I said no, but the supplier said

9
00:01:19,363 --> 00:01:20,781
it's customary.

10
00:01:21,323 --> 00:01:23,784
Ms. Joo... Come on, Ms. Joo.

11
00:01:24,577 --> 00:01:26,412
Please, listen to me.

12
00:01:27,705 --> 00:01:28,789
Let me off just this once.

13
00:01:29,873 --> 00:01:32,376
My kids are young, and my wife
quit her job to care for them.

14
00:01:32,459 --> 00:01:34,253
I'm all they have right now.

15
00:01:35,004 --> 00:01:36,297
Please, just this one time.

16
00:01:38,007 --> 00:01:40,759
You should've thought of your wife
and kids before taking the kickback.

17
00:01:41,135 --> 00:01:42,970
Don't use them
as a sentimental excuse.

18
00:01:43,262 --> 00:01:44,305
What was that?

19
00:01:46,015 --> 00:01:47,016
Hey, you.

20
00:02:02,740 --> 00:02:04,074
Know your limits.

21
00:02:04,658 --> 00:02:07,161
A cornered mouse can bite the cat.

22
00:02:17,421 --> 00:02:18,422
Darn it!

23
00:02:25,679 --> 00:02:26,930
What are you staring at?

24
00:02:29,391 --> 00:02:31,560
You weren't hoping
I'd get slapped, were you?

25
00:02:43,238 --> 00:02:44,615
<i>She's such a freak.</i>

26
00:02:49,203 --> 00:02:50,746
<i>Joo In-a couldn't possibly be</i>
<i>having an affair.</i>

27
00:02:51,372 --> 00:02:53,457
<i>- It can't be.</i>
- Mr. Noh.

28
00:02:57,836 --> 00:02:58,837
Yes?

29
00:03:02,549 --> 00:03:04,051
I thought you wanted to talk to me.

30
00:03:05,386 --> 00:03:06,387
Oh, well...

31
00:03:06,470 --> 00:03:07,805
<i>All right, for now...</i>

32
00:03:08,639 --> 00:03:11,600
<i>Let's backtrack strategically</i>
<i>until I've grasped the situation.</i>

33
00:03:13,644 --> 00:03:14,978
I wanted to apologize.

34
00:03:16,313 --> 00:03:18,315
I was rude at karaoke yesterday.

35
00:03:20,025 --> 00:03:21,777
I'm really sorry, Ms. Joo.

36
00:03:28,075 --> 00:03:29,118
I get it.

37
00:03:29,993 --> 00:03:32,246
I was a bit indifferent
and insensitive.

38
00:03:32,621 --> 00:03:35,374
I put someone like you
in charge of very limited duties.

39
00:03:36,041 --> 00:03:37,084
You must've been frustrated.

40
00:03:38,711 --> 00:03:39,712
Well...

41
00:03:41,755 --> 00:03:43,674
I'll give you more work.

42
00:03:44,967 --> 00:03:46,009
Sure.

43
00:04:00,983 --> 00:04:02,484
Wait, Mr. Noh.

44
00:04:03,110 --> 00:04:04,319
Why are you doing this?

45
00:04:07,197 --> 00:04:08,240
Oh, dear.

46
00:04:08,699 --> 00:04:10,617
Why did you have to go and...

47
00:04:11,660 --> 00:04:13,412
Why did you take her on?

48
00:04:16,081 --> 00:04:18,167
You really need to be careful.

49
00:04:18,250 --> 00:04:19,668
Seeing how she handled Mr. Seo

50
00:04:19,752 --> 00:04:21,587
made me realize
how she got called "JJCC."

51
00:04:22,087 --> 00:04:24,923
"Jeer Joo, Chaos Comes."

52
00:04:25,007 --> 00:04:26,967
That spells JJCC.

53
00:04:27,050 --> 00:04:28,510
JEER JOO, CHAOS COMES

54
00:04:28,594 --> 00:04:30,387
Gosh, just thinking about it...

55
00:04:31,930 --> 00:04:33,015
Mr. Noh.

56
00:04:34,600 --> 00:04:35,768
I'll leave this here.

57
00:04:36,018 --> 00:04:37,311
Since you're at it.

58
00:04:37,394 --> 00:04:39,480
You know I'm rooting for you, right?

59
00:04:39,855 --> 00:04:40,898
Stay strong.

60
00:04:46,695 --> 00:04:48,238
Jeez...

61
00:05:09,551 --> 00:05:10,636
My gosh.

62
00:05:34,409 --> 00:05:36,829
What the heck?

63
00:05:37,704 --> 00:05:39,331
Darn it all.

64
00:05:47,631 --> 00:05:49,383
JJCC, my foot.

65
00:05:50,467 --> 00:05:53,220
She's just an employee
like everyone else.

66
00:05:54,680 --> 00:05:56,098
REPORTING MS. JOO IN-A

67
00:05:56,181 --> 00:05:57,432
MS. JOO IN-A IS INVOLVED

68
00:05:57,516 --> 00:05:58,976
IN AN INAPPROPRIATE
WORKPLACE RELATIONSHIP

69
00:06:00,936 --> 00:06:02,187
<i>Yes.</i>

70
00:06:02,271 --> 00:06:05,315
<i>If that report turns out to be true</i>

71
00:06:06,149 --> 00:06:08,735
<i>that means I'll have what I need</i>
<i>to take Joo In-a down.</i>

72
00:06:10,153 --> 00:06:11,238
<i>This could be</i>

73
00:06:12,322 --> 00:06:13,991
<i>my opportunity.</i>

74
00:06:16,243 --> 00:06:17,661
Fine, Joo In-a.

75
00:06:18,579 --> 00:06:19,872
I'll take you on.

76
00:06:21,039 --> 00:06:23,458
Let's see who comes to a grizzly end.

77
00:06:37,264 --> 00:06:40,100
EPISODE 3:
A WOMAN WITH A TWIST

78
00:06:45,230 --> 00:06:46,315
<i>A workplace is a battlefield.</i>

79
00:06:47,774 --> 00:06:50,611
<i>Every single day,</i>
<i>we fight hard to survive and win.</i>

80
00:06:53,196 --> 00:06:54,781
<i>The fundamental rule of war is IFF.</i>

81
00:06:56,116 --> 00:06:57,659
<i>Identifying friend or foe.</i>

82
00:07:00,329 --> 00:07:01,330
<i>However...</i>

83
00:07:02,205 --> 00:07:03,248
<i>Good morning.</i>

84
00:07:03,832 --> 00:07:05,792
Ma'am, you colored your hair.

85
00:07:06,209 --> 00:07:07,836
You look 20 years younger.

86
00:07:08,086 --> 00:07:09,087
Hello.

87
00:07:09,796 --> 00:07:12,883
Sang-hyeon, you drank too much.
Soothe yourself or you'll get sick.

88
00:07:12,966 --> 00:07:15,302
<i>Identifying friend and foe at work</i>

89
00:07:15,802 --> 00:07:16,845
<i>is not at all easy.</i>

90
00:07:18,138 --> 00:07:20,057
<i>Some foes look like friends.</i>

91
00:07:20,432 --> 00:07:21,892
I never see you around.

92
00:07:21,975 --> 00:07:23,226
We should meet up soon.

93
00:07:23,644 --> 00:07:26,188
Your team and mine
could exchange info.

94
00:07:26,480 --> 00:07:28,190
Yes, sure. That would be nice.

95
00:07:28,357 --> 00:07:31,109
Let's meet for a drink another time.

96
00:07:31,193 --> 00:07:32,194
Sounds good.

97
00:07:33,070 --> 00:07:34,237
Yes, take care.

98
00:07:36,406 --> 00:07:38,617
- Oh, my gosh.
<i>- Today's friend</i>

99
00:07:39,284 --> 00:07:40,494
<i>could become tomorrow's foe.</i>

100
00:07:40,577 --> 00:07:42,287
Why are you pushing this on your own?

101
00:07:42,371 --> 00:07:43,580
You just clocked in?

102
00:07:43,664 --> 00:07:45,832
I do this every day.

103
00:07:45,916 --> 00:07:47,042
Even so.

104
00:07:47,125 --> 00:07:49,044
Be careful. You might hurt your back.

105
00:07:49,127 --> 00:07:50,879
Don't you worry about my back.

106
00:07:51,380 --> 00:07:53,840
Pushing this cart takes know-how,
not brute strength.

107
00:07:53,924 --> 00:07:55,717
- You do this.
- Oh, my gosh.

108
00:07:57,636 --> 00:07:59,513
This is almost scientific.

109
00:08:00,055 --> 00:08:02,140
It's nice to have some help.

110
00:08:03,517 --> 00:08:07,020
TEAM LEADER MOO KWANG-IL

111
00:08:12,234 --> 00:08:13,485
<i>But one thing is clear.</i>

112
00:08:14,695 --> 00:08:16,321
<i>The moment you identify a foe</i>

113
00:08:17,114 --> 00:08:18,699
<i>that is exactly what they become.</i>

114
00:08:29,918 --> 00:08:30,919
<i>As of now</i>

115
00:08:31,628 --> 00:08:33,296
<i>I will sharpen my blade quietly</i>

116
00:08:34,172 --> 00:08:35,298
<i>for my archenemy.</i>

117
00:08:35,382 --> 00:08:36,550
NEW FOLDER: NONAME

118
00:08:36,633 --> 00:08:39,511
<i>And plan a critical blow to Joo In-a.</i>

119
00:08:42,389 --> 00:08:43,849
Ms. Joo In-a.

120
00:08:44,683 --> 00:08:48,020
You asked to be excluded
from the executive staff meeting.

121
00:08:48,395 --> 00:08:51,189
Yes, Haemu's Audit Team
is an audit team only in name.

122
00:08:51,273 --> 00:08:53,025
Our tasks are not independent.

123
00:08:53,400 --> 00:08:55,152
We need to renew
our chain of command.

124
00:08:55,569 --> 00:08:58,238
We are fully under the control
of management for now.

125
00:08:59,573 --> 00:09:01,241
That almost hurts to hear.

126
00:09:02,617 --> 00:09:04,036
I can't approve your request.

127
00:09:05,078 --> 00:09:06,413
I would like for you

128
00:09:07,789 --> 00:09:09,082
to be under my control.

129
00:09:13,420 --> 00:09:15,130
Please reconsider my request.

130
00:09:16,465 --> 00:09:18,216
Well, I have a lot of work
to catch up on.

131
00:09:18,300 --> 00:09:19,634
I will excuse myself.

132
00:09:28,935 --> 00:09:30,562
She's as independent
as she needs to be.

133
00:09:30,645 --> 00:09:32,147
Shall I hear from HR next?

134
00:09:35,942 --> 00:09:37,611
Okay, so...

135
00:09:38,195 --> 00:09:39,404
President Jeon wants to reinstate

136
00:09:40,655 --> 00:09:43,116
Managing Director Jeon Sung-yeol
to the head office.

137
00:09:43,575 --> 00:09:46,495
He called me himself this morning.

138
00:09:46,578 --> 00:09:48,622
Yes, I'm aware of that.

139
00:09:50,207 --> 00:09:51,249
You are, right?

140
00:09:51,750 --> 00:09:54,252
I knew you'd be aware
of the situation.

141
00:09:54,336 --> 00:09:55,962
You are the vice president.

142
00:09:56,421 --> 00:10:00,258
Still, you should've run it by me
before bringing this to the meeting.

143
00:10:00,592 --> 00:10:01,593
It's a sensitive matter.

144
00:10:03,303 --> 00:10:04,971
I apologize. That was careless of me.

145
00:10:06,681 --> 00:10:08,058
To be honest, personally

146
00:10:09,059 --> 00:10:11,311
the risk of reinstating
Managing Director Jeon

147
00:10:11,603 --> 00:10:14,064
right after the end
of his probation period

148
00:10:14,648 --> 00:10:16,274
is quite concerning.

149
00:10:22,614 --> 00:10:23,657
Is it the President?

150
00:10:29,621 --> 00:10:30,831
PRESIDENT JEON

151
00:10:37,796 --> 00:10:39,381
Hello, Father. It's Jae-yeol.

152
00:10:40,465 --> 00:10:41,633
Did I call the wrong person?

153
00:10:41,716 --> 00:10:44,761
<i>I apologize. We were in a meeting,</i>
<i>so I answered her phone.</i>

154
00:10:44,845 --> 00:10:46,179
Sign the form.

155
00:10:47,305 --> 00:10:48,348
The thing is...

156
00:10:51,143 --> 00:10:52,602
HR voiced their concern.

157
00:10:53,603 --> 00:10:55,355
It's still a bit early.

158
00:10:55,438 --> 00:10:57,274
Some will criticize us
for putting on a show...

159
00:10:57,357 --> 00:10:58,817
<i>Haven't you seen</i>
<i>Haemu Construction's stocks?</i>

160
00:10:59,067 --> 00:11:00,277
You must acknowledge what's due.

161
00:11:00,861 --> 00:11:01,945
Don't make me repeat myself.

162
00:11:18,503 --> 00:11:21,214
Thanks for working hard today.
See you tomorrow.

163
00:11:21,298 --> 00:11:23,091
- Goodbye.
- Take care.

164
00:11:25,385 --> 00:11:26,761
Who wants to have dinner with me?

165
00:11:27,095 --> 00:11:28,513
My wife wants me to eat out.

166
00:11:30,849 --> 00:11:31,850
No one?

167
00:11:32,559 --> 00:11:34,227
- See you tomorrow.
- Yes, bye.

168
00:11:34,311 --> 00:11:35,562
- Goodbye.
- There's no one.

169
00:11:35,854 --> 00:11:37,856
Are you all trying to lose weight?

170
00:11:38,273 --> 00:11:41,109
Yes, sure. Got it.

171
00:11:58,001 --> 00:11:59,002
RECORDING, REFRAIN FROM TOUCHING

172
00:11:59,628 --> 00:12:01,880
Project No Name,
following the target.

173
00:12:35,163 --> 00:12:36,915
Is she going straight home?

174
00:13:28,049 --> 00:13:30,552
One triangle <i>gimbap, </i>a can of beer

175
00:13:32,178 --> 00:13:33,305
and a box of digestive medicine?

176
00:13:38,977 --> 00:13:40,312
My gosh.

177
00:13:43,523 --> 00:13:44,649
What are you, mister?

178
00:13:44,899 --> 00:13:46,860
Are you a stalker? A beggar?

179
00:13:50,989 --> 00:13:52,032
Did you hear the news?

180
00:13:52,282 --> 00:13:54,242
The VP's stepbrother
Managing Director Jeon Sung-yeol

181
00:13:54,326 --> 00:13:55,618
is coming back here.

182
00:13:56,202 --> 00:13:59,497
They say the president
favors him over the VP.

183
00:14:00,373 --> 00:14:02,876
Is it because
he's the current wife's son?

184
00:14:02,959 --> 00:14:04,294
This is top secret.

185
00:14:04,377 --> 00:14:06,296
The VP's birth mother.

186
00:14:06,546 --> 00:14:09,299
She was basically thrown out
because of a mental illness.

187
00:14:09,507 --> 00:14:11,509
They called her
a disgrace to the family.

188
00:14:13,011 --> 00:14:15,680
There's even talk
that they think it's hereditary.

189
00:14:15,764 --> 00:14:17,474
- Then the VP...
- Come on, now.

190
00:14:17,807 --> 00:14:20,727
Aren't you two too young
to have a prejudice like that?

191
00:14:21,770 --> 00:14:24,564
If Director Jeon does come back

192
00:14:24,647 --> 00:14:27,817
all we have to do
is decide whose side to take.

193
00:14:28,234 --> 00:14:29,444
Wouldn't it be better

194
00:14:29,944 --> 00:14:32,655
to side with the managing director?

195
00:14:33,114 --> 00:14:36,451
The current VP is in charge
only in title.

196
00:14:36,534 --> 00:14:37,702
He doesn't have a stake in Haemu.

197
00:14:39,496 --> 00:14:40,538
Hey, guys.

198
00:14:41,831 --> 00:14:42,874
It's not like that.

199
00:14:43,792 --> 00:14:45,210
You never know.

200
00:14:45,293 --> 00:14:48,088
The VP has an influential wife.

201
00:14:48,880 --> 00:14:50,882
His father-in-law owns Sesan Group.

202
00:14:50,965 --> 00:14:53,676
The President arranged that marriage
because he needed something.

203
00:14:53,760 --> 00:14:55,387
He has to be wary of them.

204
00:14:55,470 --> 00:14:56,554
You're right.

205
00:14:56,638 --> 00:14:58,431
Then we really don't know
what'll happen.

206
00:14:58,515 --> 00:14:59,724
What I can say for sure is

207
00:14:59,808 --> 00:15:03,686
our company is about to see
the biggest storm in history.

208
00:15:04,145 --> 00:15:05,438
You should be careful.

209
00:15:11,027 --> 00:15:12,487
- Hey, Mr. Moo.
- What?

210
00:15:13,154 --> 00:15:14,906
- Come see me.
- What for?

211
00:15:14,989 --> 00:15:16,574
- Follow me.
- Why?

212
00:15:18,410 --> 00:15:20,120
I packed this for you.

213
00:15:20,203 --> 00:15:22,122
- What is this?
- We made them

214
00:15:22,372 --> 00:15:25,125
for the executives,
and there were a lot of leftovers.

215
00:15:25,792 --> 00:15:27,877
Your wife is looking after twins.

216
00:15:28,169 --> 00:15:30,296
She won't have the time
to cook for herself.

217
00:15:30,380 --> 00:15:31,714
Take some home for her.

218
00:15:32,465 --> 00:15:35,718
Gosh, she's going to taste
some fancy food, thanks to you.

219
00:15:36,719 --> 00:15:37,846
My word.

220
00:15:38,054 --> 00:15:39,639
There's one more thing.

221
00:15:39,722 --> 00:15:41,808
It's not much.
Buy your kids some clothes.

222
00:15:41,891 --> 00:15:43,393
My kids have enough clothes.

223
00:15:43,476 --> 00:15:45,437
You gave too much money

224
00:15:45,520 --> 00:15:47,939
when you attended
my father's funeral.

225
00:15:48,314 --> 00:15:50,233
I didn't get to thank you then.
Take the money.

226
00:15:50,316 --> 00:15:51,818
- It's fine. It wasn't much.
- No.

227
00:15:51,901 --> 00:15:53,528
- You don't need to.
- Take it.

228
00:15:53,611 --> 00:15:54,988
- I don't want it.
- Don't say no.

229
00:15:55,071 --> 00:15:56,698
- You need to stop, ma'am.
- Take it.

230
00:15:56,781 --> 00:15:58,032
Don't do that.

231
00:15:58,658 --> 00:15:59,742
- No.
- What's this?

232
00:16:00,118 --> 00:16:01,578
Can you not do this?

233
00:16:03,455 --> 00:16:04,581
What kind of scene is this?

234
00:16:08,460 --> 00:16:09,586
This is insane.

235
00:16:10,128 --> 00:16:11,212
What are they doing out here?

236
00:16:36,154 --> 00:16:38,281
A triangle <i>gimbap </i>and a can of beer.

237
00:16:38,948 --> 00:16:40,533
That's all she buys every time?

238
00:16:40,992 --> 00:16:43,786
Yes, I thought the lady

239
00:16:43,870 --> 00:16:45,121
just had a small appetite.

240
00:16:45,580 --> 00:16:46,998
I see.

241
00:16:50,251 --> 00:16:52,295
Does she not like eating?

242
00:16:55,632 --> 00:16:56,883
Did she ever

243
00:16:57,967 --> 00:16:59,594
come here with a man?

244
00:17:00,470 --> 00:17:03,056
No, I never even saw her
with a woman.

245
00:17:03,139 --> 00:17:05,183
- She's always on her own.
- Is she?

246
00:17:08,311 --> 00:17:11,189
You must be really smart, Rhena.

247
00:17:11,272 --> 00:17:12,649
You remember all the customers.

248
00:17:12,732 --> 00:17:14,943
No, I only remember because it's her.

249
00:17:15,026 --> 00:17:16,819
Because it's her? How come?

250
00:17:17,195 --> 00:17:18,446
She's pretty.

251
00:17:18,530 --> 00:17:20,949
What? She's pretty?
Joo... That woman?

252
00:17:21,032 --> 00:17:22,075
Yes.

253
00:17:32,544 --> 00:17:33,753
Well, I guess.

254
00:17:33,836 --> 00:17:35,797
We all have
different beauty standards.

255
00:17:36,172 --> 00:17:39,384
She must be what you consider pretty.

256
00:17:44,764 --> 00:17:47,267
Hey, do you want another ice cream?

257
00:17:47,809 --> 00:17:49,143
No, buy me wine.

258
00:17:52,897 --> 00:17:54,983
- Rhena, I drove...
- To share with my boyfriend.

259
00:17:59,571 --> 00:18:01,698
<i>Where would the princesses</i>
<i>like to go?</i>

260
00:18:03,283 --> 00:18:04,409
Where shall we go?

261
00:18:04,826 --> 00:18:06,452
- That way.
- That way?

262
00:18:06,536 --> 00:18:07,996
Here we go.

263
00:18:10,123 --> 00:18:11,457
We've reached the ocean.

264
00:18:11,541 --> 00:18:12,542
Where do we go now?

265
00:18:13,459 --> 00:18:14,460
Backward?

266
00:18:19,132 --> 00:18:20,717
Where shall we go now? Which way?

267
00:18:21,467 --> 00:18:22,927
- This way?
- Girls.

268
00:18:23,886 --> 00:18:25,388
It's past your bedtime.

269
00:18:25,471 --> 00:18:27,223
Go and brush your teeth.

270
00:18:27,307 --> 00:18:29,225
Mommy Monster's angry. Get away.

271
00:18:29,601 --> 00:18:31,144
Run away.

272
00:18:32,103 --> 00:18:33,521
Gosh. I feel so hot.

273
00:18:33,938 --> 00:18:37,442
Oh, dear. It's hard work
raising young kids at my age.

274
00:18:37,525 --> 00:18:38,860
Save your energy.

275
00:18:39,277 --> 00:18:41,446
You need to work
until they finish university.

276
00:18:41,529 --> 00:18:42,614
Oh, my gosh.

277
00:18:43,239 --> 00:18:45,033
Oh, dear. My poor knees.

278
00:18:46,909 --> 00:18:48,161
- Honey.
- Yes?

279
00:18:48,995 --> 00:18:51,205
Your cafeteria food is delicious.

280
00:18:51,289 --> 00:18:52,457
Large companies are the best.

281
00:18:52,540 --> 00:18:53,833
- Do you like it?
- Yes.

282
00:18:54,250 --> 00:18:56,127
It tastes even better
because someone else made it.

283
00:18:57,462 --> 00:18:58,588
Take your time.

284
00:18:58,671 --> 00:18:59,922
Can you bring food home
every now and then?

285
00:19:01,049 --> 00:19:02,175
I'll do that.

286
00:19:04,260 --> 00:19:05,720
It's great to see you enjoy it.

287
00:19:06,095 --> 00:19:07,096
Here's some water.

288
00:19:14,520 --> 00:19:15,563
You're home.

289
00:19:16,272 --> 00:19:18,816
You're late. Did you meet someone?

290
00:19:20,193 --> 00:19:21,277
No, I worked late.

291
00:19:26,282 --> 00:19:28,326
Why did you spend so much
at a convenience store?

292
00:19:28,409 --> 00:19:29,452
Oh, that?

293
00:19:30,328 --> 00:19:32,121
The part-timer
bullied me into paying.

294
00:19:33,414 --> 00:19:34,415
Gosh.

295
00:19:34,874 --> 00:19:36,626
Gosh, ten condoms?

296
00:19:37,293 --> 00:19:38,378
What?

297
00:19:42,256 --> 00:19:43,758
Jeez, that kid...

298
00:19:44,175 --> 00:19:45,468
I wonder if her parents know

299
00:19:45,760 --> 00:19:47,136
what she's up to instead of studying.

300
00:19:48,346 --> 00:19:51,224
If they heard, they'd be relieved
that she knows enough

301
00:19:51,307 --> 00:19:52,767
to take precautions.

302
00:19:53,935 --> 00:19:56,145
They must be really in love
if they need ten boxes.

303
00:19:58,439 --> 00:20:00,817
Hey, ten boxes is nothing.

304
00:20:01,734 --> 00:20:04,278
You know... Back in my day...

305
00:20:15,498 --> 00:20:17,792
Is that what you're eating
for dinner?

306
00:20:18,084 --> 00:20:19,168
Why didn't you order takeout?

307
00:20:19,252 --> 00:20:21,671
I had dinner.
This is a late-night snack.

308
00:20:23,715 --> 00:20:25,800
Do you want one?
It was buy one, get one free.

309
00:20:34,016 --> 00:20:36,394
KIMCHI AND SPICY PORK TRIANGLE <i>GIMBAP</i>

310
00:20:37,019 --> 00:20:38,020
Hey.

311
00:20:39,772 --> 00:20:41,315
I know someone

312
00:20:41,399 --> 00:20:43,901
who eats just one triangle <i>gimbap</i>
for dinner every day.

313
00:20:46,154 --> 00:20:47,572
What kind of person would do that?

314
00:20:47,655 --> 00:20:49,240
They must be poor.

315
00:20:49,323 --> 00:20:50,533
No, it's not that.

316
00:20:51,743 --> 00:20:53,119
They make a decent amount.

317
00:20:55,580 --> 00:20:56,581
Then maybe

318
00:20:58,207 --> 00:20:59,709
they just eat to survive.

319
00:21:00,168 --> 00:21:03,129
Some people eat the bare minimum
so they don't die.

320
00:21:04,088 --> 00:21:05,965
They might look like they have a lot

321
00:21:06,799 --> 00:21:08,676
but they feel empty inside.

322
00:21:09,677 --> 00:21:10,678
That's why

323
00:21:11,220 --> 00:21:13,097
they don't feel full
even though they eat.

324
00:21:13,806 --> 00:21:16,058
They don't feel energized
even though they sleep.

325
00:21:22,398 --> 00:21:23,566
Who are you talking about?

326
00:21:24,317 --> 00:21:26,778
It can't be you, seeing you're eating
a late-night snack.

327
00:21:32,200 --> 00:21:34,076
- Hey, Seung-hee.
<i>- A-jeong.</i>

328
00:21:34,368 --> 00:21:36,162
<i>Sorry for calling late at night.</i>

329
00:21:36,245 --> 00:21:37,872
<i>Did you check out</i>
<i>the anonymous bulletin board?</i>

330
00:21:38,164 --> 00:21:40,833
<i>There are endless posts</i>
<i>about the VP and his stepbrother.</i>

331
00:21:42,627 --> 00:21:44,378
GET SOME POPCORN READY
SO DO THEY HAVE DIFFERENT MOMS?

332
00:21:44,462 --> 00:21:46,464
A LEGENDARY SITUATION AT HAEMU
GOODBYE TO J'S SUPPORTERS

333
00:21:49,759 --> 00:21:51,302
Information Team!

334
00:21:51,385 --> 00:21:53,554
Do something about it!

335
00:21:53,805 --> 00:21:56,307
Take down the posts
as soon as they come up.

336
00:21:56,599 --> 00:21:58,184
Or block certain keywords.

337
00:21:58,267 --> 00:22:00,186
Can't you block posts
that say "birth mom"?

338
00:22:00,269 --> 00:22:02,522
That won't stop people
from using other terms.

339
00:22:03,439 --> 00:22:05,233
If we block every post on this topic

340
00:22:05,316 --> 00:22:08,319
they'll complain that HR
is censoring public opinion.

341
00:22:08,820 --> 00:22:12,198
And work.com
can't be controlled or censored.

342
00:22:13,908 --> 00:22:15,159
Be reasonable.

343
00:22:15,952 --> 00:22:17,286
I'm not asking you
to censor anything.

344
00:22:18,663 --> 00:22:19,956
That can't be the only solution.

345
00:22:22,124 --> 00:22:24,377
We each have just one mouth.

346
00:22:25,503 --> 00:22:26,671
Can't you

347
00:22:27,296 --> 00:22:28,965
come up with an idea?

348
00:22:34,220 --> 00:22:35,638
This is driving me insane.

349
00:22:37,223 --> 00:22:38,975
- Sir.
- What?

350
00:22:39,559 --> 00:22:40,726
Can you take a look at this?

351
00:22:41,018 --> 00:22:42,061
What is it?

352
00:22:43,104 --> 00:22:44,814
Someone posted it yesterday.

353
00:22:46,482 --> 00:22:48,192
How about we use this
to our advantage?

354
00:22:48,818 --> 00:22:50,319
It could gain some interest.

355
00:22:50,903 --> 00:22:52,154
"Middle-aged romance"?

356
00:22:52,864 --> 00:22:53,865
Hang on.

357
00:22:54,490 --> 00:22:57,618
I know this jawline from somewhere.

358
00:22:59,453 --> 00:23:00,538
Team Leader Moo?

359
00:23:00,830 --> 00:23:02,123
Hey, Moo...

360
00:23:03,457 --> 00:23:05,668
Good find, Ms. Oh. Can you move over?

361
00:23:06,335 --> 00:23:08,462
Yes, let's put this to good use.

362
00:23:09,171 --> 00:23:12,174
Let's see.
A middle-aged woman. Madam...

363
00:23:12,383 --> 00:23:13,801
How does "Madam Killer" sound?

364
00:23:14,093 --> 00:23:15,261
Well...

365
00:23:15,678 --> 00:23:17,013
- That's a bit...
- Then...

366
00:23:17,889 --> 00:23:20,266
"An audit team leader's affair."

367
00:23:20,600 --> 00:23:21,726
Is that more provocative?

368
00:23:21,809 --> 00:23:24,145
Isn't it a bit much
to reveal his identity?

369
00:23:24,228 --> 00:23:26,606
Revealing his identity
will increase the impact.

370
00:23:27,523 --> 00:23:29,567
You don't have to worry.

371
00:23:29,942 --> 00:23:31,819
This guy's a PNU.

372
00:23:33,070 --> 00:23:34,363
<i>"PNU"?</i>

373
00:23:34,447 --> 00:23:36,949
<i>Yes, it's a term HR uses.</i>

374
00:23:40,536 --> 00:23:42,288
<i>It refers to someone who is useless.</i>

375
00:23:42,663 --> 00:23:44,415
<i>What? That's so mean.</i>

376
00:23:45,082 --> 00:23:46,834
When a printed report has many pages

377
00:23:47,168 --> 00:23:50,630
you can fold the corner like this
so the big bosses can flip easily.

378
00:23:50,713 --> 00:23:52,173
Don't you think they'd appreciate it?

379
00:23:52,715 --> 00:23:53,841
You're so thoughtful.

380
00:23:55,927 --> 00:23:57,178
Are you serious?

381
00:23:58,095 --> 00:23:59,347
- What?
- Never mind.

382
00:23:59,889 --> 00:24:01,682
This is how I became a team leader.

383
00:24:01,766 --> 00:24:03,225
Must be why I'm still a manager.

384
00:24:06,604 --> 00:24:08,105
I think it looks great.

385
00:24:14,028 --> 00:24:17,365
SEARCH HAEMU GROUP: JOO IN-A

386
00:24:17,865 --> 00:24:19,742
JOO IN-A'S PERSONNEL FILE

387
00:24:22,870 --> 00:24:23,871
SEARCH REQUEST FOR LEISURE STIPEND

388
00:24:23,955 --> 00:24:25,915
NO REQUEST FOR LEISURE STIPEND

389
00:24:27,625 --> 00:24:28,793
NO APPROVED REQUEST FOR LEAVE

390
00:24:28,876 --> 00:24:29,919
NO RECORD OF COMPANY CARD USE

391
00:24:43,633 --> 00:24:46,761
<i>She doesn't go on leave</i>
<i>or claim any benefits.</i>

392
00:24:46,844 --> 00:24:48,137
<i>And she doesn't eat much.</i>

393
00:24:49,764 --> 00:24:51,766
<i>What does she live for?</i>

394
00:24:56,562 --> 00:24:57,855
Did I get you?

395
00:24:57,939 --> 00:24:59,524
You almost fell onto your backside.

396
00:25:00,274 --> 00:25:01,526
<i>Is this what gives her joy?</i>

397
00:25:02,151 --> 00:25:03,236
I scored.

398
00:25:04,987 --> 00:25:08,157
Wait, were you the one
looking after this plant?

399
00:25:08,908 --> 00:25:10,076
Oh, yes.

400
00:25:10,159 --> 00:25:12,203
I water it whenever I think of it.

401
00:25:12,745 --> 00:25:15,790
You're surprisingly thoughtful,
Mr. Noh.

402
00:25:16,416 --> 00:25:17,583
It's quite pretty.

403
00:25:20,128 --> 00:25:21,337
It smells, too.

404
00:25:33,266 --> 00:25:34,559
<i>She's pretty.</i>

405
00:25:35,184 --> 00:25:37,854
<i>Well, I guess you can't say</i>
<i>she isn't pretty.</i>

406
00:25:39,439 --> 00:25:40,440
What was that?

407
00:25:41,524 --> 00:25:43,401
I think you just smiled at me.

408
00:25:44,402 --> 00:25:45,611
That's because...

409
00:25:46,070 --> 00:25:48,698
Do I look funny to you, Mr. Noh?

410
00:25:48,781 --> 00:25:50,074
No, it's not that.

411
00:25:50,158 --> 00:25:52,076
I found your prank hilarious.

412
00:25:52,160 --> 00:25:53,411
When you jump-scared me.

413
00:25:54,203 --> 00:25:55,872
The more I think about it,
the funnier it is.

414
00:25:57,623 --> 00:26:00,042
The more I get to know you,
the more I see your humor.

415
00:26:02,837 --> 00:26:04,797
You caught on?

416
00:26:05,965 --> 00:26:07,675
I knew it. You have the wit.

417
00:26:08,217 --> 00:26:10,261
I don't get
why people are afraid of me.

418
00:26:10,344 --> 00:26:12,472
I'm hilarious, aren't I?

419
00:26:13,431 --> 00:26:14,557
You are.

420
00:26:14,640 --> 00:26:16,017
You get my wit.

421
00:26:19,270 --> 00:26:21,272
Oh, my gosh.

422
00:26:22,064 --> 00:26:25,443
My blood sugar must be going low.

423
00:26:26,694 --> 00:26:30,406
Where was Ms. Yoon's snack box?

424
00:26:32,241 --> 00:26:33,284
What's going on?

425
00:26:33,367 --> 00:26:36,162
Ms. Yoon,
The snack box is in here, right?

426
00:26:36,537 --> 00:26:37,663
Your box of snacks

427
00:26:38,206 --> 00:26:39,707
full of candies and chocolates.

428
00:26:40,166 --> 00:26:41,542
The drawer's locked.

429
00:26:42,960 --> 00:26:43,961
Ms. Yoon.

430
00:26:44,587 --> 00:26:46,839
Did you not like
my getting into your snack box?

431
00:26:47,673 --> 00:26:49,801
You should've told me so.

432
00:26:50,176 --> 00:26:53,471
Locking it away is harsh on your part
and embarrassing for me.

433
00:26:53,930 --> 00:26:55,723
I kept dropping hints
that I didn't like it.

434
00:26:56,474 --> 00:26:58,434
You failed to pick up on them.

435
00:26:59,811 --> 00:27:01,062
Oh, dear. I feel bad.

436
00:27:01,521 --> 00:27:02,939
- My gosh.
- What's wrong?

437
00:27:04,941 --> 00:27:07,527
Mr. Moo,
I think you need to see this.

438
00:27:10,613 --> 00:27:11,989
IF THEY DO THIS IN PUBLIC,
THEN IN PRIVATE...

439
00:27:12,073 --> 00:27:13,074
OH, MY GOSH! SPARE ME!

440
00:27:14,992 --> 00:27:17,912
Wow, you're the talk of the town.

441
00:27:22,667 --> 00:27:23,668
MADAM KILLER IS HILARIOUS

442
00:27:23,751 --> 00:27:25,795
"The Madam Killer"? Goodness.

443
00:27:25,878 --> 00:27:27,380
You're a killer, too, Mr. Moo?

444
00:27:27,463 --> 00:27:29,674
I had a nickname similar to that.

445
00:27:29,757 --> 00:27:31,217
It's not at all like that.

446
00:27:31,300 --> 00:27:33,761
Why would I go around killing ladies?

447
00:27:34,095 --> 00:27:38,307
The photo was taken at an angle
that made us look suspicious.

448
00:27:38,641 --> 00:27:39,684
We were...

449
00:27:40,184 --> 00:27:43,104
That lady and I don't have
any kind of relationship.

450
00:27:44,230 --> 00:27:48,901
I can't believe that smoke
sometimes does appear without a fire.

451
00:27:49,110 --> 00:27:52,530
This isn't just some smoke.
The blaze could take us all down.

452
00:27:55,157 --> 00:27:56,284
Assistant Manager Ahn Min-su.

453
00:27:56,492 --> 00:27:57,785
Yes, Ms. Joo?

454
00:28:03,207 --> 00:28:05,418
I need you to look into this.

455
00:28:05,751 --> 00:28:07,962
Mr. Noh usually takes the PM cases

456
00:28:08,045 --> 00:28:09,964
but that would be inappropriate
as they're teammates.

457
00:28:10,381 --> 00:28:12,133
Pardon? Whose case am I taking on?

458
00:28:12,466 --> 00:28:13,926
Mr. Moo's case.

459
00:28:14,552 --> 00:28:15,553
- Gosh...
- Wait.

460
00:28:16,679 --> 00:28:18,180
Are you going to investigate this?

461
00:28:18,264 --> 00:28:19,473
Of course, I must.

462
00:28:19,557 --> 00:28:21,851
The case is big enough
that everyone's talking about it.

463
00:28:21,934 --> 00:28:24,478
Ms. Joo. It's just a random incident.

464
00:28:24,562 --> 00:28:25,980
It can't even be called a case.

465
00:28:26,063 --> 00:28:28,399
I'm innocent. You know what I'm like.

466
00:28:28,482 --> 00:28:29,567
Yes, Mr. Moo.

467
00:28:29,650 --> 00:28:31,903
That's all you have to say
when you're interviewed.

468
00:28:32,695 --> 00:28:35,239
Drop everything you were working on
until the case is concluded.

469
00:28:35,573 --> 00:28:37,199
If anything needs to be approved...

470
00:28:37,909 --> 00:28:39,535
Manager Cha Sung-tae,
that's your duty now.

471
00:28:41,746 --> 00:28:42,747
That's all.

472
00:28:53,716 --> 00:28:55,760
Why are you still here?
You're dismissed.

473
00:28:56,844 --> 00:28:58,804
Oh, dear. It really isn't anything.

474
00:28:59,889 --> 00:29:01,349
It's really nothing.

475
00:29:02,892 --> 00:29:03,935
My goodness...

476
00:29:30,836 --> 00:29:32,838
WRITTEN STATEMENT

477
00:29:51,273 --> 00:29:52,733
I'm home.

478
00:29:57,154 --> 00:29:58,155
Is everyone in bed?

479
00:30:00,116 --> 00:30:01,158
Are the girls asleep?

480
00:30:06,831 --> 00:30:10,751
OUR AUDIT TEAM LEADER'S CHEATING

481
00:30:11,502 --> 00:30:12,962
They say this is you.

482
00:30:13,587 --> 00:30:14,588
Yes.

483
00:30:17,425 --> 00:30:18,551
The food

484
00:30:19,635 --> 00:30:21,345
you brought me last night.

485
00:30:22,596 --> 00:30:23,848
Did she give it to you?

486
00:30:26,892 --> 00:30:29,270
- Did she?
- No, it's not like that.

487
00:30:31,022 --> 00:30:32,732
How should I explain?

488
00:30:44,201 --> 00:30:46,037
Based on how she treated Mr. Moo

489
00:30:46,370 --> 00:30:48,330
she wouldn't do anything.
wrong or immoral

490
00:30:52,001 --> 00:30:53,461
Am I wasting my time?

491
00:31:00,301 --> 00:31:02,053
Hang on. She's not going home?

492
00:31:02,970 --> 00:31:04,055
Darn it.

493
00:32:18,712 --> 00:32:20,756
<i>Okay. This is it.</i>

494
00:32:38,065 --> 00:32:39,984
SEON DRAWING CLASS,
RECREATIONAL CLASS FOR ADULTS

495
00:32:40,067 --> 00:32:41,235
"Recreational art"?

496
00:32:45,156 --> 00:32:46,157
Excuse me.

497
00:32:47,032 --> 00:32:48,325
Are you going inside?

498
00:32:49,201 --> 00:32:50,828
No, sorry.

499
00:32:58,878 --> 00:33:00,880
<i>Was drawing her hobby?</i>

500
00:33:11,223 --> 00:33:13,267
- Hello.
- Morning.

501
00:33:17,104 --> 00:33:18,439
Oh, my goodness!

502
00:33:18,856 --> 00:33:20,232
Mr. Moo!

503
00:33:20,858 --> 00:33:22,276
Oh, dear. My bad.

504
00:33:22,568 --> 00:33:23,861
My gosh.

505
00:33:24,445 --> 00:33:25,487
Goodness me.

506
00:33:27,364 --> 00:33:29,283
Oh, dear.

507
00:33:37,374 --> 00:33:39,835
Did you spend the night here?

508
00:33:40,211 --> 00:33:42,004
Did you argue
with your wife last night?

509
00:33:42,087 --> 00:33:44,298
Why sleep here
when we have a night duty room?

510
00:33:44,381 --> 00:33:46,300
What are you doing here, Mr. Moo?

511
00:33:46,383 --> 00:33:47,801
Good morning, Ms. Joo.

512
00:33:48,010 --> 00:33:51,263
Something came up,
and I couldn't go home last night.

513
00:33:51,513 --> 00:33:53,849
I couldn't think
of anywhere else to go.

514
00:33:53,933 --> 00:33:55,851
So you decided to come to the office?

515
00:33:58,729 --> 00:34:01,398
You don't seem to know
where to draw the line.

516
00:34:02,024 --> 00:34:05,027
You take cafeteria food home
and come here to sleep at night.

517
00:34:08,989 --> 00:34:09,990
Please leave

518
00:34:10,741 --> 00:34:11,742
immediately.

519
00:34:12,284 --> 00:34:13,619
- Sorry?
- The subject of investigation

520
00:34:13,702 --> 00:34:16,288
does not have free access
to the office while it's ongoing.

521
00:34:16,830 --> 00:34:19,166
This was far too careless of you
as the head of an audit team.

522
00:34:20,209 --> 00:34:21,293
Ms. Pyun.

523
00:34:21,585 --> 00:34:24,171
Request a restriction of his access
to General Affairs.

524
00:34:25,297 --> 00:34:28,300
- Do we have to go that far...
- Going that far is our ground rule.

525
00:34:29,969 --> 00:34:31,845
And Audit Teams are here
to strictly abide by the rules.

526
00:34:32,554 --> 00:34:33,597
Yes, of course.

527
00:34:34,056 --> 00:34:36,725
I should've thought this through.
I'll leave right away.

528
00:34:37,726 --> 00:34:38,936
Goodness, I'm sorry.

529
00:34:39,645 --> 00:34:41,146
Please let me just get my shoes.

530
00:34:42,189 --> 00:34:43,232
Sorry.

531
00:34:43,315 --> 00:34:45,818
Ms. Pyun, here's my employee ID.

532
00:34:46,694 --> 00:34:48,320
Mr. Baek, can you put the box away?

533
00:34:48,946 --> 00:34:51,824
Goodness. I'm sorry. I apologize.

534
00:34:51,907 --> 00:34:54,076
I'm so sorry.

535
00:35:12,469 --> 00:35:13,887
Mister, you're Moo Kwang-il,
aren't you?

536
00:35:14,388 --> 00:35:16,473
- Yes, who are you?
- Don't you know me?

537
00:35:17,057 --> 00:35:18,767
We met at my grandfather's funeral.

538
00:35:20,644 --> 00:35:23,981
Yes, you're Ms. Eom's eldest son.
It's nice to see you.

539
00:35:25,816 --> 00:35:27,943
I should've known
when you were acting nosy.

540
00:35:28,777 --> 00:35:30,529
Work colleague, my foot.

541
00:35:31,071 --> 00:35:32,948
Who would care
about an outsourced worker's family?

542
00:35:33,032 --> 00:35:34,033
You were coming onto her!

543
00:35:35,159 --> 00:35:38,120
There must be
a huge misunderstanding.

544
00:35:38,203 --> 00:35:40,497
A misunderstanding?
That's easy for you to say.

545
00:35:40,998 --> 00:35:43,375
My mom lost her job
and can't make a living anymore!

546
00:35:43,751 --> 00:35:45,836
You'll probably be fine
because you're a big corporate guy

547
00:35:46,420 --> 00:35:48,422
but my mom is an expendable! Get it?

548
00:35:48,505 --> 00:35:49,923
Let go of me!

549
00:35:50,215 --> 00:35:51,717
- Sir.
- Goodness!

550
00:35:51,800 --> 00:35:53,635
Did she seem that easy to you,
you punk?

551
00:35:54,303 --> 00:35:56,347
- Hey, goodness. Wait a second.
- Let go of me!

552
00:35:56,805 --> 00:35:57,973
Let go!

553
00:35:58,057 --> 00:35:59,350
- You can't do this here.
- Let go!

554
00:36:00,726 --> 00:36:02,895
You went around acting nosy
like you were my dad. This is great.

555
00:36:02,978 --> 00:36:05,731
You can now be my dad
and make a living for me, okay?

556
00:36:05,814 --> 00:36:08,025
Dad... Father...

557
00:36:08,108 --> 00:36:09,151
- Sir.
- Darn it.

558
00:36:12,404 --> 00:36:14,239
Will you let go of me?

559
00:36:14,490 --> 00:36:15,991
Just let go!

560
00:36:16,075 --> 00:36:17,451
Please calm down.

561
00:36:18,327 --> 00:36:19,370
Let go of me!

562
00:36:20,120 --> 00:36:22,206
How dare you hit on my poor mother?

563
00:36:22,289 --> 00:36:24,583
How can you be so vulgar
at your age? Darn it!

564
00:36:24,666 --> 00:36:27,044
I knew he was like that
when he acted too nice.

565
00:36:46,438 --> 00:36:49,024
It was a temporary reaction
due to stress

566
00:36:49,108 --> 00:36:50,651
so please get a good rest.

567
00:36:51,443 --> 00:36:53,862
Would you like anything to eat?

568
00:37:01,036 --> 00:37:02,663
Come on, let's leave.
Get a good rest.

569
00:37:05,207 --> 00:37:07,501
I've never seen Mr. Moo
look so disheartened before.

570
00:37:07,751 --> 00:37:09,586
He must feel awful.

571
00:37:10,295 --> 00:37:13,257
People took his act of kindness
and called it an affair and whatnot.

572
00:37:13,340 --> 00:37:15,426
They all blamed him
like they were hunting him down.

573
00:37:15,509 --> 00:37:17,177
It is too petty a matter
to even make excuses for.

574
00:37:17,594 --> 00:37:19,430
Jeez, this is awful.

575
00:37:20,180 --> 00:37:22,015
The bulletin has become crazier
in the meantime.

576
00:37:22,766 --> 00:37:25,018
"No one is kind enough to visit
the cafeteria lady's dad's funeral."

577
00:37:25,310 --> 00:37:26,603
They say it's 100 percent an affair.

578
00:37:26,687 --> 00:37:28,564
Man, that's just too much.

579
00:37:28,939 --> 00:37:30,941
Why are people like this? Why?

580
00:37:32,401 --> 00:37:33,610
- Hello.
- Hello.

581
00:37:33,694 --> 00:37:35,404
Is Mr. Moo inside?

582
00:37:36,280 --> 00:37:38,866
- Is he all right?
- What do you think?

583
00:37:39,450 --> 00:37:41,160
- Do you have the result?
- Yes.

584
00:37:41,243 --> 00:37:43,120
It doesn't seem like
they were having an affair

585
00:37:43,954 --> 00:37:46,290
but Mr. Moo will be reprimanded...

586
00:37:46,373 --> 00:37:48,250
If he didn't have an affair,
why should he be?

587
00:37:48,333 --> 00:37:50,169
After all, there was a commotion
within the company

588
00:37:50,252 --> 00:37:52,629
and our reputation fell
when the word got out, so...

589
00:37:52,713 --> 00:37:54,548
How is that his fault?

590
00:37:54,631 --> 00:37:57,259
- He's the victim of a witch hunt!
- Yes.

591
00:37:57,342 --> 00:38:00,179
I agree with you, but it's Ms. Joo.

592
00:38:01,096 --> 00:38:02,764
- Excuse me.
- Wait a second.

593
00:38:03,265 --> 00:38:05,267
Mr. Moo can't afford
to be shocked anymore right now.

594
00:38:06,018 --> 00:38:07,102
Also, we cannot accept

595
00:38:07,728 --> 00:38:09,313
this disciplinary action.

596
00:38:09,897 --> 00:38:11,565
How will that change anything?

597
00:38:12,065 --> 00:38:15,319
Let's go and ask Ms. Joo
to withdraw this as a team.

598
00:38:16,737 --> 00:38:18,739
Yes, it's time to protest.

599
00:38:20,741 --> 00:38:23,535
Well, the thing is...
It's embarrassing to bring this up.

600
00:38:24,286 --> 00:38:27,414
I lost my fortune in crypto before
and couldn't pay my credit card bill

601
00:38:27,498 --> 00:38:28,540
but Mr. Moo helped me out.

602
00:38:28,957 --> 00:38:32,961
And she should do her part as a boss
to cover for her team in these times.

603
00:38:33,045 --> 00:38:35,464
I wonder if she'd do that
when I do something wrong

604
00:38:35,547 --> 00:38:37,299
- so it feels very personal.
- You're right.

605
00:38:37,841 --> 00:38:39,301
This isn't just Mr. Moo's business.

606
00:38:39,384 --> 00:38:41,261
This is everyone's problem.

607
00:38:41,345 --> 00:38:44,765
Things seem
a bit heated up right now.

608
00:38:45,140 --> 00:38:47,059
Why don't we calm down
and use our common sense to think...

609
00:38:47,142 --> 00:38:48,810
Do you want to stay out of this?

610
00:38:49,686 --> 00:38:53,232
Why? Do you not want to take part
because you're the Audit Team's ace?

611
00:39:04,576 --> 00:39:06,578
COME TO THE ROOFTOP! PLEASE
FROM AUDIT TEAM 3

612
00:39:50,664 --> 00:39:52,124
It was a phrase
I haven't heard for a while.

613
00:39:52,207 --> 00:39:53,625
"Come to the rooftop."

614
00:39:55,127 --> 00:39:56,503
So are you ganging up on me?

615
00:39:57,296 --> 00:39:58,714
It's kind of cheap
to outnumber me like this.

616
00:39:59,047 --> 00:40:00,257
Why don't a few of you cross over?

617
00:40:06,763 --> 00:40:07,764
Ms. Joo.

618
00:40:08,640 --> 00:40:10,892
We would like to speak to you
as a team

619
00:40:11,393 --> 00:40:13,312
regarding Mr. Moo.

620
00:40:15,856 --> 00:40:18,525
Withdraw the disciplinary action
against him, please.

621
00:40:19,026 --> 00:40:20,193
- Please do that!
- Please do that!

622
00:40:21,153 --> 00:40:23,822
He's already suffering
from all kinds of malicious rumors.

623
00:40:23,905 --> 00:40:27,492
The notice of his disciplinary action
will only make matters worse.

624
00:40:27,868 --> 00:40:30,495
He wasn't at fault to begin with.
It was a misunderstanding.

625
00:41:06,823 --> 00:41:07,991
Oh, my gosh!

626
00:41:17,084 --> 00:41:18,210
Never mind.

627
00:41:19,419 --> 00:41:20,671
My legs were hurting.

628
00:41:26,593 --> 00:41:28,303
Now, where were we?

629
00:41:28,387 --> 00:41:31,014
Yes, that Mr. Moo
didn't do anything wrong.

630
00:41:33,684 --> 00:41:35,852
You're right.
There was no infidelity between them.

631
00:41:36,853 --> 00:41:40,190
But he took cafeteria food out,
which is considered company property

632
00:41:40,273 --> 00:41:41,900
and exchanged
a considerable amount of money

633
00:41:41,983 --> 00:41:43,110
with an outsourced staff member

634
00:41:43,443 --> 00:41:45,362
causing a controversy
inside and outside the office.

635
00:41:46,405 --> 00:41:47,489
I think

636
00:41:48,073 --> 00:41:49,574
reprimanding him sounds adequate.

637
00:41:50,701 --> 00:41:52,953
Will anyone care
about the whole story?

638
00:41:53,912 --> 00:41:57,165
They'll brand him for infidelity,
thinking the suspicions are right

639
00:41:57,666 --> 00:41:59,084
because of the disciplinary action.

640
00:42:02,587 --> 00:42:05,507
Then will glossing over this matter
put everything to its rest?

641
00:42:06,466 --> 00:42:08,510
"The Audit Team nitpicks over
every little detail with us

642
00:42:08,593 --> 00:42:09,803
but they cover for their own."

643
00:42:10,846 --> 00:42:12,639
Wouldn't people insult
the entire team?

644
00:42:12,723 --> 00:42:15,434
You're our boss
before you're the Head of Audit.

645
00:42:15,934 --> 00:42:18,353
And shouldn't you draw the line
and protect us in times like these

646
00:42:18,437 --> 00:42:19,980
if you truly are our boss?

647
00:42:20,564 --> 00:42:23,525
How can we have faith in this company
if you treat us like this?

648
00:42:30,741 --> 00:42:33,618
You don't need to have faith to work.
We aren't a church.

649
00:42:35,120 --> 00:42:37,873
You come to work
because you get paid to be here!

650
00:42:38,582 --> 00:42:40,876
And because we are paid,
I will fulfill my responsibility

651
00:42:40,959 --> 00:42:43,086
and Mr. Moo must fulfill his own.

652
00:42:49,176 --> 00:42:50,218
"Draw the line"?

653
00:42:51,803 --> 00:42:54,347
That line is there
because you are not to step over it.

654
00:43:08,111 --> 00:43:10,280
White Blood Cell, you're something.

655
00:43:10,363 --> 00:43:12,324
Never mind. Go ahead.

656
00:43:13,742 --> 00:43:15,368
I think we stepped off the deep end.

657
00:43:18,914 --> 00:43:20,457
We can't end it like this.

658
00:43:21,291 --> 00:43:22,918
The negotiation is off

659
00:43:23,919 --> 00:43:25,420
so we must act as a group.

660
00:43:25,504 --> 00:43:27,923
There's no talking to her,
so we must show her with our action.

661
00:43:43,772 --> 00:43:45,065
Excuse me.

662
00:43:45,982 --> 00:43:49,194
Ms. Joo, the entire team
took the rest of the day off.

663
00:43:49,736 --> 00:43:52,447
They called it a kind of a strike.

664
00:43:53,740 --> 00:43:55,659
They want you to retract
Mr. Moo's disciplinary action.

665
00:44:01,623 --> 00:44:04,501
Goodness. There's a fly in here.
It's a dung fly.

666
00:44:06,795 --> 00:44:08,755
Is the office not tidy enough?

667
00:44:11,842 --> 00:44:12,843
Sorry?

668
00:44:14,511 --> 00:44:15,554
Yes.

669
00:44:17,013 --> 00:44:18,223
That was it?

670
00:44:19,266 --> 00:44:20,809
All right. Bye.

671
00:44:22,561 --> 00:44:23,728
Why? What did Ms. Joo say?

672
00:44:26,356 --> 00:44:27,566
Nothing.

673
00:44:29,568 --> 00:44:30,819
She caught a fly and turned around.

674
00:44:30,902 --> 00:44:32,195
- That's it?
- Yes.

675
00:44:32,279 --> 00:44:33,905
She must think we're a huge joke.

676
00:44:33,989 --> 00:44:36,199
How can she not respond in any way
even after our group strike?

677
00:44:36,283 --> 00:44:37,784
That's why she's Joo In-a.

678
00:44:37,868 --> 00:44:40,036
I expected this, but how could she
not be bothered at all?

679
00:44:40,120 --> 00:44:41,121
Whatever. Let's keep it going.

680
00:44:41,204 --> 00:44:42,622
Take tomorrow off, too.

681
00:44:42,706 --> 00:44:43,707
Wait a minute.

682
00:44:44,541 --> 00:44:46,543
If Ms. Joo doesn't approve
our leave request

683
00:44:46,626 --> 00:44:48,253
it'll be considered
unauthorized absence.

684
00:44:49,754 --> 00:44:50,964
Wait, in that case...

685
00:44:51,298 --> 00:44:54,134
Is there a possibility
that we'll also get punishment?

686
00:44:54,551 --> 00:44:58,054
Come on.
Ms. Joo can't be that inconsiderate.

687
00:44:58,138 --> 00:44:59,973
Isn't that why we're here now?

688
00:45:04,853 --> 00:45:05,896
In that case

689
00:45:06,521 --> 00:45:09,274
why don't one of us go upstairs
and do a quick vibe check?

690
00:45:09,357 --> 00:45:11,234
And check how Ms. Joo is doing.

691
00:45:12,277 --> 00:45:13,570
Do you want to go, Mr. Noh?

692
00:45:13,945 --> 00:45:14,946
Me?

693
00:45:15,030 --> 00:45:18,241
DOES ANYBODY KNOW
WHAT HAPPENED TO THE MADAM KILLER?

694
00:45:18,950 --> 00:45:19,951
Lastly

695
00:45:20,327 --> 00:45:22,913
Managing Director Jeon Sung-yeol
will return to the headquarters.

696
00:45:23,997 --> 00:45:25,457
I expect you to show him support.

697
00:45:36,217 --> 00:45:37,886
Now it's official.

698
00:45:37,969 --> 00:45:39,387
It must be what the president wants.

699
00:45:39,471 --> 00:45:40,597
Of course, it is.

700
00:45:40,680 --> 00:45:42,849
Jeez, there are two suns
radiating up in our sky.

701
00:45:49,814 --> 00:45:50,899
It'll happen, anyway.

702
00:45:57,489 --> 00:45:58,573
Ms. Boo.

703
00:46:03,244 --> 00:46:04,287
It's Se-young.

704
00:46:06,706 --> 00:46:07,791
Se-young.

705
00:46:09,542 --> 00:46:11,836
Isn't it about time
that you took a measure for Mr. Moo?

706
00:46:12,462 --> 00:46:14,965
HR and Information Office
is in charge of the intranet.

707
00:46:15,882 --> 00:46:17,801
I already shared the result
of our investigation

708
00:46:17,884 --> 00:46:19,427
that the infidelity was groundless.

709
00:46:20,512 --> 00:46:21,805
But the bulletin
is still going strong.

710
00:46:21,888 --> 00:46:23,348
People are like that.

711
00:46:24,057 --> 00:46:25,892
No one cares about the truth.

712
00:46:25,976 --> 00:46:27,060
Exactly.

713
00:46:27,686 --> 00:46:30,105
So I'm asking HR
to delete those posts accordingly.

714
00:46:33,108 --> 00:46:34,651
We've been a little busy.

715
00:46:35,777 --> 00:46:36,861
I'll look into it, though.

716
00:46:38,113 --> 00:46:39,656
It's because of Mr. Jeon, isn't it?

717
00:46:42,450 --> 00:46:44,160
The bulletin always has
posts about him

718
00:46:44,244 --> 00:46:46,079
so you're diverting people
and manipulating opinions.

719
00:46:47,205 --> 00:46:48,999
I've noticed it a while ago

720
00:46:49,082 --> 00:46:50,583
but HR was doing what HR does

721
00:46:51,042 --> 00:46:52,502
so I was going to observe.

722
00:46:53,294 --> 00:46:54,337
But you know

723
00:46:55,588 --> 00:46:57,424
I've had enough of your nonsense.

724
00:46:57,799 --> 00:46:58,842
Nonsense?

725
00:46:59,592 --> 00:47:02,554
Hey. Do you think HR is a joke?

726
00:47:06,558 --> 00:47:07,600
Anyway.

727
00:47:08,184 --> 00:47:10,228
But in the end,
I guess I have to thank him.

728
00:47:10,937 --> 00:47:13,314
You always cover up a rumor
with another rumor.

729
00:47:15,442 --> 00:47:16,484
Right?

730
00:47:17,402 --> 00:47:20,071
You cover up a rumor
with another rumor, right?

731
00:47:28,538 --> 00:47:31,541
What are you doing?
Hey. Let go of me. Hey!

732
00:47:31,624 --> 00:47:32,709
You!

733
00:47:33,209 --> 00:47:36,046
Have you lost your mind?
Get over here.

734
00:47:36,463 --> 00:47:38,506
Let go of me!

735
00:47:38,590 --> 00:47:40,675
Let go! Hey!

736
00:47:41,259 --> 00:47:44,220
Let go! Let go of my hair!

737
00:47:44,304 --> 00:47:46,347
Have you lost your mind?

738
00:47:46,431 --> 00:47:48,349
Hey! Let go of me!

739
00:47:52,896 --> 00:47:55,148
Let go of my hair!

740
00:47:55,231 --> 00:47:56,733
'22 RECRUITS GROUP CHAT
1 NEW MESSAGE

741
00:47:56,816 --> 00:47:58,902
AUDIT TEAM 3 GROUP CHAT
1 NEW MESSAGE

742
00:48:00,111 --> 00:48:01,946
<i>You. Let go of me.</i>

743
00:48:02,280 --> 00:48:03,531
<i>Let go!</i>

744
00:48:20,924 --> 00:48:21,966
<i>What kind of person</i>

745
00:48:22,675 --> 00:48:24,219
<i>is Joo In-a?</i>

746
00:48:30,558 --> 00:48:32,102
<i>- No way.</i>
<i>- This is the craziest ever.</i>

747
00:48:32,185 --> 00:48:34,562
<i>- People made so many clips.</i>
<i>- Why did they fight?</i>

748
00:48:34,646 --> 00:48:35,730
<i>They've always been enemies.</i>

749
00:48:36,439 --> 00:48:37,482
<i>Everyone knew.</i>

750
00:48:39,776 --> 00:48:41,986
In the end, did everything go
according to her plan?

751
00:48:42,529 --> 00:48:43,571
<i>Right?</i>

752
00:48:43,780 --> 00:48:46,282
<i>You cover up a rumor</i>
<i>with another rumor, right?</i>

753
00:48:58,169 --> 00:48:59,254
<i>Know your limits.</i>

754
00:48:59,546 --> 00:49:02,090
A cornered mouse can bite the cat.

755
00:49:14,060 --> 00:49:15,103
Ms. Joo.

756
00:49:15,645 --> 00:49:16,855
I need to talk to you.

757
00:49:19,149 --> 00:49:21,276
Unfortunately, I'm done for the day.

758
00:49:21,818 --> 00:49:23,319
Please come to my office tomorrow.

759
00:49:24,821 --> 00:49:25,989
What the heck is this complaint?

760
00:49:26,072 --> 00:49:28,032
Wasn't the disciplinary action
more than enough?

761
00:49:28,491 --> 00:49:30,160
Are you trying

762
00:49:30,660 --> 00:49:32,871
to end someone's life?

763
00:49:34,080 --> 00:49:35,206
Let's talk.

764
00:50:08,323 --> 00:50:09,365
Anyway, Ms. Joo.

765
00:50:10,909 --> 00:50:12,202
Do you have to keep

766
00:50:13,494 --> 00:50:15,038
the rest of your fingers folded in?

767
00:50:18,750 --> 00:50:20,043
I wanted to make it easier for you.

768
00:50:22,003 --> 00:50:23,046
Right.

769
00:50:24,505 --> 00:50:26,591
Goodness. Of all those fingers,
you hurt this one.

770
00:50:36,434 --> 00:50:37,477
All done.

771
00:50:38,269 --> 00:50:40,980
I only gave you first aid,
so please see a doctor tomorrow.

772
00:50:41,064 --> 00:50:43,691
Okay. You're my savior today, so...

773
00:50:45,318 --> 00:50:47,195
Please enjoy, sir.

774
00:50:52,075 --> 00:50:53,868
Is this what your life is worth?

775
00:50:53,952 --> 00:50:55,745
It's not for my life.
It's for my finger.

776
00:50:57,247 --> 00:50:58,957
I look stylish and powerful.

777
00:50:59,457 --> 00:51:00,500
I like this one.

778
00:51:01,459 --> 00:51:02,543
"This one"?

779
00:51:02,961 --> 00:51:04,295
Does this happen to you often?

780
00:51:04,379 --> 00:51:05,880
This is kind of cute, actually.

781
00:51:06,714 --> 00:51:08,716
Back in the day,
someone destroyed my computer

782
00:51:08,800 --> 00:51:11,302
and another employee fled after
splashing my seat with superglue.

783
00:51:11,636 --> 00:51:13,805
And a CEO of a corrupt business
struck my head with a golf club.

784
00:51:14,305 --> 00:51:15,390
I probably have a scar here.

785
00:51:15,473 --> 00:51:17,517
Right here. Can you see it?

786
00:51:18,017 --> 00:51:19,102
It's from my surgery back then.

787
00:51:19,769 --> 00:51:21,020
While I was working abroad

788
00:51:21,104 --> 00:51:23,273
the local gang
even threatened me with a knife.

789
00:51:24,315 --> 00:51:25,400
So I

790
00:51:26,359 --> 00:51:27,443
picked up a gun.

791
00:51:32,824 --> 00:51:34,284
That's why you're Joo-niper.

792
00:51:35,076 --> 00:51:37,537
So that rumor was true?
Did you really shoot a person?

793
00:51:38,162 --> 00:51:39,289
What do you think?

794
00:51:42,750 --> 00:51:44,002
No, I don't want to know.

795
00:51:54,053 --> 00:51:55,096
Ms. Joo.

796
00:51:56,806 --> 00:51:58,766
About your fight with the Head of HR.

797
00:52:04,564 --> 00:52:05,606
No, never mind.

798
00:52:12,113 --> 00:52:13,323
Are you perverted?

799
00:52:13,990 --> 00:52:16,451
- What?
- Do you get off on getting hated?

800
00:52:16,993 --> 00:52:19,203
I know it's hard not to make enemies
when you're working

801
00:52:19,287 --> 00:52:20,747
but you can try to make less.

802
00:52:21,456 --> 00:52:22,749
But it seems like

803
00:52:23,750 --> 00:52:25,418
you want to get hated

804
00:52:25,752 --> 00:52:26,878
even more than you actually want.

805
00:52:29,380 --> 00:52:31,299
No one wants to be hated.

806
00:52:32,091 --> 00:52:34,886
However, there are times
when I must position myself.

807
00:52:35,511 --> 00:52:37,555
I must either be a saint
or a villain.

808
00:52:38,389 --> 00:52:39,974
If I stay in the middle,
I get no work done

809
00:52:40,058 --> 00:52:42,268
lose my popularity,
and nothing works out.

810
00:52:43,394 --> 00:52:45,021
Do you know who your worst boss is?

811
00:52:46,814 --> 00:52:47,899
A non-committal jerk.

812
00:52:50,151 --> 00:52:51,194
Yes.

813
00:52:51,444 --> 00:52:53,112
You definitely are committed to one.

814
00:53:02,372 --> 00:53:03,539
But it must be lonely

815
00:53:05,375 --> 00:53:06,709
to have your sincerity misunderstood.

816
00:53:11,839 --> 00:53:13,174
Did you misunderstand me?

817
00:53:13,716 --> 00:53:14,759
How so?

818
00:53:18,429 --> 00:53:19,931
That you were a cold-hearted person

819
00:53:20,014 --> 00:53:23,726
who don't care about others' feelings
to accomplish your goals.

820
00:53:26,312 --> 00:53:27,480
Well, I thought so.

821
00:53:29,565 --> 00:53:31,609
But you seem to be someone
who does things your own way

822
00:53:32,777 --> 00:53:34,612
when you do something
you believe is right.

823
00:53:37,365 --> 00:53:39,617
People may misunderstand you
because of that

824
00:53:40,410 --> 00:53:42,036
and you put yourself
in a hard position

825
00:53:42,703 --> 00:53:43,830
but you do not back out

826
00:53:44,580 --> 00:53:45,665
or make excuses.

827
00:53:47,875 --> 00:53:49,127
I doubt it's easy

828
00:53:51,129 --> 00:53:52,255
to always live like that.

829
00:54:01,305 --> 00:54:02,348
Wow.

830
00:54:03,015 --> 00:54:04,600
You know how to talk, Mr. Noh.

831
00:54:05,560 --> 00:54:06,936
I was a bit moved just now.

832
00:54:10,231 --> 00:54:13,276
Anyway, don't you think
the misunderstanding was harsh?

833
00:54:13,693 --> 00:54:15,278
You practically thought
I was a psychopath.

834
00:54:15,361 --> 00:54:16,988
You do come across that way.

835
00:54:17,572 --> 00:54:18,739
Me?

836
00:54:18,823 --> 00:54:20,491
But I love people.

837
00:54:20,783 --> 00:54:22,326
Even personality tests say
I'm an extrovert

838
00:54:22,410 --> 00:54:24,162
- like a cute little puppy.
- Cute little puppy?

839
00:54:24,662 --> 00:54:27,290
People are intimidated by you!

840
00:54:30,209 --> 00:54:31,294
You can't have this.

841
00:54:32,295 --> 00:54:34,088
Look at this.

842
00:54:34,172 --> 00:54:36,132
This is why you come off like that.

843
00:54:36,716 --> 00:54:38,050
Give it back.

844
00:54:38,634 --> 00:54:41,095
I'm a big psychopath,
so I can't do that.

845
00:54:45,391 --> 00:54:47,185
It's even better
because I took it back from you.

846
00:54:48,019 --> 00:54:49,228
Don't finish it. It's mine...

847
00:54:58,863 --> 00:55:00,698
You skipped dinner today.

848
00:55:01,407 --> 00:55:02,783
You should eat,
even if you don't want to.

849
00:55:03,201 --> 00:55:04,911
Okay. Leave it there and go.

850
00:55:12,251 --> 00:55:13,753
It's the key to the studio apartment.

851
00:55:15,129 --> 00:55:16,672
Thank you for everything.

852
00:55:18,007 --> 00:55:19,300
While moving out

853
00:55:19,550 --> 00:55:22,094
I stole a bottle of your hard liquor
as a souvenir.

854
00:55:23,054 --> 00:55:24,055
Is that okay?

855
00:55:27,683 --> 00:55:28,976
I don't mind.

856
00:55:30,561 --> 00:55:31,604
But why the sudden change?

857
00:55:32,480 --> 00:55:34,690
Has your family matter been resolved?

858
00:55:35,107 --> 00:55:36,192
No.

859
00:55:36,943 --> 00:55:37,944
I just

860
00:55:39,987 --> 00:55:41,822
don't want to stay there anymore.

861
00:55:44,242 --> 00:55:45,576
Then where are you staying?

862
00:55:46,786 --> 00:55:48,829
- Is it safe?
- I'm not telling.

863
00:55:50,456 --> 00:55:52,708
I want you to be concerned

864
00:55:53,834 --> 00:55:54,877
about me.

865
00:56:25,825 --> 00:56:27,201
He wrapped it up so neatly.

866
00:57:30,806 --> 00:57:31,807
Jae-yeol!

867
00:57:52,203 --> 00:57:53,371
I'll see you more often now.

868
00:57:53,954 --> 00:57:54,997
Jae-yeol.

869
00:57:56,332 --> 00:57:57,375
Sure.

870
00:58:02,672 --> 00:58:04,465
It's been a while
since I've written an apology

871
00:58:04,548 --> 00:58:06,050
and I found the fun in it.

872
00:58:12,765 --> 00:58:14,558
- Mr. Moo.
- Yes?

873
00:58:14,642 --> 00:58:16,352
You're a special man who have worked

874
00:58:16,435 --> 00:58:18,729
in 12 teams, 5 branches,
and 3 different subsidiaries.

875
00:58:19,730 --> 00:58:21,649
You're highly interested
in every aspect of the company

876
00:58:21,732 --> 00:58:23,234
so you have information and network.

877
00:58:24,276 --> 00:58:26,362
It makes you a perfect candidate
to take up Audit Team Three

878
00:58:26,445 --> 00:58:28,239
a team that receives
dozens of complains a day.

879
00:58:29,198 --> 00:58:30,199
Above all

880
00:58:30,574 --> 00:58:32,410
you're a good leader
to your team members

881
00:58:32,660 --> 00:58:34,537
who each have a big personality.

882
00:58:34,829 --> 00:58:38,332
Goodness, I appreciate
your words of consolation.

883
00:58:38,416 --> 00:58:39,417
However

884
00:58:40,376 --> 00:58:41,544
that's a double-edged sword.

885
00:58:42,128 --> 00:58:43,963
Your sound personality

886
00:58:44,046 --> 00:58:46,340
sometimes doesn't fit
to be the leader of the Audit Team.

887
00:58:47,133 --> 00:58:49,468
Members of other departments are
the subjects of our investigation.

888
00:58:50,219 --> 00:58:51,721
Make use of them as your intel

889
00:58:51,804 --> 00:58:53,848
but please try to keep them
in a proper distance.

890
00:58:56,642 --> 00:58:58,769
How can I make use of people
as my intel?

891
00:58:58,853 --> 00:58:59,937
I'm not a spy.

892
00:59:01,647 --> 00:59:02,690
Goodness.

893
00:59:03,482 --> 00:59:04,525
Well, Ms. Joo.

894
00:59:05,025 --> 00:59:06,819
I crunched some numbers

895
00:59:07,945 --> 00:59:10,823
and realized that during weekdays,
I can only play with my daughters

896
00:59:10,906 --> 00:59:12,450
two hours a day at most.

897
00:59:13,117 --> 00:59:15,619
But I must sit here
and work with my colleagues

898
00:59:15,703 --> 00:59:17,705
for nine hours a day.

899
00:59:18,497 --> 00:59:19,707
And in those hours

900
00:59:19,957 --> 00:59:21,751
if I do not keep
a friendly relationship

901
00:59:22,042 --> 00:59:23,669
with my colleagues

902
00:59:24,336 --> 00:59:25,671
it would make my life

903
00:59:27,548 --> 00:59:28,883
too meaningless.

904
00:59:29,925 --> 00:59:30,926
In the future

905
00:59:31,510 --> 00:59:34,805
I will do my best to help out
if I find another colleague in need

906
00:59:35,347 --> 00:59:38,642
and gladly take any food they bring
if they decide to do that.

907
00:59:39,268 --> 00:59:40,936
I'll write up another apology
when that happens.

908
00:59:43,522 --> 00:59:44,565
I'm sorry.

909
00:59:45,858 --> 00:59:48,861
Anyway, I will do my job
without a big ambition

910
00:59:49,236 --> 00:59:52,364
but for a long time
while enjoying my time here.

911
00:59:59,121 --> 01:00:01,832
If you have nothing more to say,
then please excuse me.

912
01:00:03,209 --> 01:00:04,251
All right.

913
01:00:07,254 --> 01:00:08,464
Oh, Ms. Joo.

914
01:00:11,008 --> 01:00:14,762
By any chance,
did you pull out Ms. Boo's hair

915
01:00:15,554 --> 01:00:17,431
for my sake?

916
01:00:18,766 --> 01:00:20,059
Is that important?

917
01:00:21,101 --> 01:00:23,229
No. Please excuse me.

918
01:00:32,279 --> 01:00:33,322
<i>Perhaps</i>

919
01:00:34,406 --> 01:00:36,700
<i>distinguishing between</i>
<i>your friend and foe at work</i>

920
01:00:42,915 --> 01:00:44,834
<i>is not that important.</i>

921
01:00:49,338 --> 01:00:50,464
I don't work here anymore.

922
01:00:51,715 --> 01:00:53,968
I got a better job elsewhere,
so don't worry about me.

923
01:00:54,260 --> 01:00:56,136
Goodness,
you're such a talented person.

924
01:00:56,220 --> 01:00:57,263
Good for you.

925
01:00:59,223 --> 01:01:01,892
Please give me a call
when your twins get married.

926
01:01:02,351 --> 01:01:03,853
I may not give you as much

927
01:01:03,936 --> 01:01:05,437
but I want to show you
my token of sincerity.

928
01:01:05,521 --> 01:01:06,564
Of course.

929
01:01:11,151 --> 01:01:12,528
- Stay healthy.
- Thank you.

930
01:01:12,903 --> 01:01:14,071
Thank you for your hard work.

931
01:01:20,119 --> 01:01:21,495
<i>What's more important is...</i>

932
01:01:22,663 --> 01:01:26,667
HEAD OF AUDIT

933
01:01:26,750 --> 01:01:29,169
Gosh, the air in this office
is way too dry.

934
01:01:29,253 --> 01:01:31,213
I should tidy this up a little.

935
01:01:33,465 --> 01:01:35,426
Are you done?
Ms. Joo, here's your coffee.

936
01:01:35,843 --> 01:01:37,011
Goodness.

937
01:01:40,472 --> 01:01:41,807
Let me dry that off.

938
01:01:48,272 --> 01:01:50,816
Shoo!

939
01:01:52,735 --> 01:01:54,695
Shoo.

940
01:01:56,864 --> 01:01:57,948
Excuse us.

941
01:02:01,619 --> 01:02:03,704
<i>...the discretion</i>
<i>not to turn your friend into a foe.</i>

942
01:02:04,705 --> 01:02:06,290
By any chance, do you feel hot?

943
01:02:06,373 --> 01:02:07,708
Should I fan you?

944
01:02:07,791 --> 01:02:09,335
- Stronger.
- Stronger wind.

945
01:02:10,586 --> 01:02:11,712
Does that feel better?

946
01:02:23,474 --> 01:02:26,268
<i>And the determination to gladly</i>
<i>become my colleague's friend.</i>

947
01:02:27,686 --> 01:02:28,896
<i>Perhaps those are more important.</i>

948
01:02:47,122 --> 01:02:48,415
RECREATIONAL ART CLASS
TONIGHT AT 9 P.M.

949
01:02:52,336 --> 01:02:55,089
<i>Even someone who has</i>
<i>a great reputation like Mr. Moo</i>

950
01:02:55,965 --> 01:02:58,050
<i>got cornered</i>
<i>because of a single photo.</i>

951
01:03:00,094 --> 01:03:01,595
<i>Joo In-a has enemies all around her.</i>

952
01:03:06,141 --> 01:03:07,184
<i>That report.</i>

953
01:03:07,393 --> 01:03:08,936
REPORTING MS. JOO IN-A

954
01:03:09,019 --> 01:03:10,396
<i>It's probably</i>
<i>an attempt to entrap her.</i>

955
01:03:11,438 --> 01:03:13,524
All right. I need to stop here.

956
01:03:47,933 --> 01:03:49,143
Wait. Excuse me.

957
01:03:50,811 --> 01:03:52,771
Do you need that
to take a class here?

958
01:03:53,022 --> 01:03:54,356
Oh, yes.

959
01:03:55,149 --> 01:03:57,526
The club members must bring it.

960
01:03:57,776 --> 01:03:59,737
I see. Thank you.

961
01:04:07,619 --> 01:04:08,662
<i>What's going on?</i>

962
01:04:09,621 --> 01:04:11,081
<i>She wasn't carrying that thing.</i>

963
01:06:12,536 --> 01:06:15,455
FILING FOR LOVE

964
01:06:15,914 --> 01:06:18,834
GUEST APPEARANCE BY LEE JUNG-EUN

965
01:06:44,484 --> 01:06:45,611
<i>How can I act like nothing happened?</i>

966
01:06:45,694 --> 01:06:46,695
<i>It's just not the same.</i>

967
01:06:47,905 --> 01:06:49,072
<i>This is driving me crazy.</i>

968
01:06:49,156 --> 01:06:51,617
Babe, come here. Hurry.

969
01:06:52,242 --> 01:06:53,535
- Bravo!
- <i>There's</i>

970
01:06:53,619 --> 01:06:55,120
<i>definitely more to this incident.</i>

971
01:06:55,204 --> 01:06:57,831
<i>Who did you mess with</i>

972
01:06:57,915 --> 01:06:59,082
<i>to become their target?</i>

973
01:06:59,166 --> 01:07:00,667
<i>If this backfires</i>
<i>due to a careless move</i>

974
01:07:00,751 --> 01:07:01,960
<i>you could be in serious trouble.</i>

975
01:07:02,044 --> 01:07:03,170
<i>I'll make sure it doesn't backfire.</i>

976
01:07:03,253 --> 01:07:04,379
Room 1306, please.

977
01:07:04,463 --> 01:07:05,797
<i>I'm staying the night.</i>

978
01:07:05,881 --> 01:07:08,383
<i>Why are you hesitating now?</i>
<i>You've already seen it.</i>

979
01:07:09,760 --> 01:07:11,720
<i>- Could you stop staring at my body?</i>
<i>- Sorry?</i>

980
01:07:25,609 --> 01:07:27,611
Subtitles by Eunsook Youn
and Jennifer Lim
